The closing rite of the casket, begun at 20, was presided over by Cardinal Camerlengo, the Master of Liturgical Celebrations gave reading of the rogito, which was laid in the coffin at the end of the celebration. They participated in the rite, in addition to those indicated in the Notification of the Office of Liturgical Celebrations, also some family members of the deceased Pope. The celebration took place according to the prescriptions of the Romans Pontificals Ordo Exsequiarum. >
