<h2> Argentina President Javier Milei</h2>
Argentina president Javier Milei arrived at Fiumicino airport. Tomorrow the president will be in the front row to the funeral of Pope Francis, born in Argentina.&nbsp;
Real Jordan and Denmark arrived at Fiumicino
The rulers of Jordan, King Abdallah II with his wife Rania>, and Queen Mary of Denmark>, arrived at Fiumicino airport. Tomorrow, together with many other rulers, heads of state and prime ministers, will attend the funeral of Pope Francis.&nbsp;
<h2>250 thousand people paid tribute to salma</h2>
From the morning of Wednesday 23 April to 11:00 until this evening at 19:00 > they went to St. Peter's Basilica to greet Pope Francis about 250,000 people. It makes known the Vatican press room.&nbsp;
<h2>Emmanuel Macron and his wife Brigitte in S.Pietro</h2>
French President Emmanuel Macron and his wife Brigitte in San Pietro paid tribute to the psalm of Pope Francis. The head of the Elysée stopped a few minutes in front of the coffin.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> Extraordinary closures for the Conclave
The Sistine Chapel will be closed to the public on Monday, April 28, "for the needs of the Conclave," the Holy See announced. "All visits to the Vatican Gardens and the Necropolis of the Via Triumphalis> are also suspended."
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> Closed Vatican Museums in mourning
The Direction of the Museums > and Cultural Heritage >, "in expressing deep mourning and pain for the disappearance of the Holy Father", we read, that Saturday, 26 April, "the Vatican Museums > and the Museum of Castel Gandolfo > will be closed to the public, as a sign of mourning, for the funeral of the Roman Pontiff Francis".
<h2> The cardinals at the tomb of Francis at S.M.Maggiore</h2>
On Sunday afternoon at 4 pm the cardinals will go to the Basilica of Santa Maria Maggiore. After passing the Holy Door, they will visit the tomb of Pope Francis and the chapel where there is the icon of the Salus Populi Romani > and then the Vespers will be celebrated. At 18 they will return to the Vatican.&nbsp;
