Fadlun recalled among others Bruno Dell'Ariccia>, who escaped the retata of 16 October, which joined the partisans in Tivoli. Alberto Terracina>, in the Resistance of the Roman Castles, which fought between Genzano, Lanuvio and Velletri, until the liberation of Rome. Piero Cividalli>: In 1939, he fled Italy with the family for racial laws. At age 19, he volunteered in the British Army. He trained in Egypt, ready to return to his land to fight the Nazis. His face has long been that of the last Italian survivor of the Jewish Brigade >. The Jewish Brigade that landed in Naples in September 1943, building hospitals and giving refuge to refugees. That entered Rome in June '44 with the star of David> sewn on the uniform. From the Ferramonti camp to Milan, Aaron HaKodesh>. No one can take away the freedom to honor them. To tell, explain, remember. And we remember well >!” he concluded.
